        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:12PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 511 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
East Freetown, or near Marathon, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hunts Corners, Preston, Mc Donough, Plymouth, East Freetown,
Pharsalia, German, Cincinnatus, Lapeer, and Tyner.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
